Fun adventure/interrogation game. Interesting plot and characters. Good acting, environments, and cinematography. Nice music. Even with a mere handful of characters and locations, the world feels rich, and teeming with possibilities. The keyboard controls are strange, and my Xbox 360 controller didn't work, but I managed to get used to it all in good time. I sunk a solid 8 hours into this game, and when I solved the mystery, it left me wanting more! Not something I can say after spending the same price (or more) at the theatre. ;}

